data.title: Cody Cook - 2018-19 - Men's Golf
data.meta_description: Cody Cook - 2018-19 (Senior): Participated in 4 events and 9 rounds and averaged 76.3 strokes per round for the Beavers... Had a season low round of 73 at the Holiday
data.text:
2018-19 (Senior): Participated in 4 events and 9 rounds and averaged 76.3 strokes per round for the Beavers... Had a season low round of 73 at the Holiday Inn Express Classic in St. Joseph, MO (10/8)... Placed in the top 20 in 2 of 4 meets this season.

2017-18 (Junior): Participated in nine events and 20 rounds and averaged 76.1 strokes per round for second on the team... Tied a career low round of 70 at the Upper Iowa Spring Invite March 30... Totaled four rounds under par on the season and placed in the top 20 four times... Earned a silver medal at the Upper Iowa Invite after firing a two-round score of 142 (72-70)... Placed 27th at the NSIC Men's Golf Championship with a score of 234 (80-82-72).

2016-17 (Sophomore): Participated in 8 events and 17 rounds averaging a score of 77.4 for the season... Placed a season high t-8th with 76 and 72 at the NSIC Spring Preview, March 25-26... Finished in the top 20 twice placing t-15th at the UIU Spring Invite, April 1-2, scoring 78 and 79 and again at the St. Cloud State Invitational, Sept. 25-26, t-13th scoring 81 and 77... Was the beavers top finisher in three different events: t-8th at NSIC Spring Preview March 25-26, t-41 at the Washburn Invitational March 13-14, and t-28 at the MWSU/Holiday Inn Express Classic October 10-11.

2015-16 (Freshman): Named to the All-NSIC Second Team... Played 17 rounds with a low score of 70 Sept. 27-28 in the second round of the 2015 Huskies Invite… Led the Beavers to a fourth place finish at the NSIC Men’s Golf Championship Oct. 5-6 and April 9-10 with a team-low score of 292 (six-over par), ranking second overall in the tournament… Averaged a score of 76.9 per round… In seven events participated in, finished within the top five once and the top 10 three times… Shot nine-over par in Bemidji State’s team win at the BSU Invitational.

Hawley High School: Cook comes to Bemidji State after a prep career during which he has been part of seven Heart O’ Lake championship teams at Hawley High School. After leading the Golden Nuggets to the Heart O’ Lakes team title in 2014, Cook was recognized as the league’s most valuable player. A Minnesota State High School League Class AA Tournament participant, Cook finished 30th in 2014 and was named to the 2014 Minnesota Class AA All-State Team. He sat 45th on the Minnesota Golf Association High School Boy’s Rankings following the 2014 season. Also a football player for Hawley High School, Cook is a lineman on both sides of the ball.

Personal: Son of Randy and Tammy Cook... Born August 6, 1996... Majoring in Sport Management while at BSU.

Career Low: 70, x2, last at Upper Iowa Spring Invite (3/30/18)
